ies and opportunities at UIC  The academic mission is further supported and implemented by the Vice Provosts  Aisha El Amin at aelami  uic Contact the Office of the Provost aelami  uic edu  n      Organizational Chart n     Contact Us  n n nFlag icon n n n n n n n nReport a UIC Policy or Procedure n Flag icon  n n nCalendar icon n n n n n n nProvost Office Hours n Calendar icon  n n nDocument icon n n n n n n n n n nProvost Communications n Document icon  n n nUser icon n n n n n n nFaculty Search Committee Training n User icon  n n nSpeech bubble icon n n n n n n nTask Force on Immigration Issues n Speech bubble icon The John Marshall Law School and UIC  Chicago s Public Law School The board of trustees of both the University of Illinois and The John Marshall Law School have voted to create UIC John Marshall Law School  In addition to providing current and prospective students with a more affordable legal education degree programs aligned with UIC strengths in disciplines such as the health sciences  engineering and technology  urban planning and public administration  the social sciences and business Read major press coverage  National Law Journal Law com Inside Higher Ed Chicago Tribune WBEZ Chicago Sun Times  n      Read more about The UIC John Marshall Law School n     Colleges and Units Reporting to the Provost College of Architecture  Design  and the Arts Interim Dean Walter Benn Michaels College of Business Administration Dean Michael Mikhail College of Education Dean Alfred Tatum College of Engineering Dean Pete Nelson Graduate College Dean Karen J  Colley Honors College Dean Ralph Keen College of Liberal Arts and Sciences Dean Astrida Orle Tantillo College of Urban Planning and Public Affairs Dean Michael A  Pagano University Library Dean Mary Case The Provost s Management Team Associate Provost Aisha El Amin Academic and Enrollment Services Vice Provost Kevin Browne Diversity Vice Provost and Associate Chancellor Amalia Pallares Faculty Affairs Vice Provo